1.--> MongoDB is a NOSql Database and it stores data in the form of objects, and sql stores data in the form of tables.

2. --> Backend contains Application Server(NodeJs) and Database(MongoDB).

3. --> Suppose ek Database hai facebook kaa, and uss Database mein users kaa data hai, ads kaa data hai, posts kaa data hai,
        toh in sabko kehte hain collections i.e. facebook ek Database hai and uss database mein sabhi users kaa data jo hoga
        woh ek collection kehlayega and advertisements(Ads) kaa bhi data hoga, toh yeh bhi ek collection kehlayega, aise hi 
        collection i.e. users ke data ke andar bhi ek agar hum individual user ko select karenge toh usko hum document
        bolenge.

        Conclusion:- Database --> Collection --> Document i.e.,database ke andar collection, and collectionke andar document

4. --> Mongoose.connect se database create hota hai.
5. --> model create se collection create hota hai.
5. --> CREATE code se hum document create karte hain. 

6. --> Mongoose humare NodeJs Server and MongoDB Server ko connect karta hai i.e. nodejs se hum databse(mongodb) ko connect
        kar sakte hain with the help of Mongoose